<item>
            <title>[SPARK-19646] binaryRecords replicates records in scala API</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-19646</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The scala sc.binaryRecords replicates one record for the entire set.&lt;br/&gt;
for example, I am trying to load the cifar binary data where in a big binary file, each 3073 represents a 32x32x3 bytes image with 1 byte for the label label. The file resides on my local filesystem.&lt;br/&gt;
.take(5) returns 5 records all the same, .collect() returns 10,000 records all the same.&lt;br/&gt;
What is puzzling is that the pyspark one works perfectly even though underneath it is calling the scala implementation.&lt;br/&gt;
I have tested this on 2.1.0 and 2.0.0&lt;/p&gt;</description>
